The paper proposes a framework for answering commonsense questions using external knowledge graphs, which involves natural language processing and machine learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with the intersection of computer science and linguistics. The paper also involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques, as well as information retrieval (cs.IR) to extract relevant information from the knowledge graphs. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel graph network module (KagNet), which falls under the sub-category of structured inference (cs.SI).
